definition.value: This is an AE which is an injury to the heart as the result of blunt trauma, typically to the anterior chest wall.

This is an AE which is a set of manifestations caused by the failure of the heart's function as a pump supporting the blood flow through the body; its signs and symptoms result from a structural and/or functional abnormality of the heart, that disrupts its filling with blood or its ejecting of it during each heart beat

This is an AE which is a syndrome defined as the new onset (de novo heart failure (HF)) or worsening (acutely decompensated heart failure (ADHF)) of symptoms and signs of HF, mostly related to systemic congestion.
This is an AE which is a long-term condition, usually kept stable by the treatment of symptoms.

This is an AE which is a term used in cardiac physiology that describes the volume of blood being pumped by the heart, by the left and right ventricle, per unit time.
This is an AE which is a defect in the structure of the heart or great vessels.

This is an AE which moved from hearts with only one ventricle connected with atria [double inlet ventricle or absent atrioventricular (AV) connection] to hearts not amenable to biventricular repair, namely hearts with two ventricles unable to sustain separately pulmonary and systemic circulations in sequence.
